<font size="2" color="#990000"><b>OP-ED </b></font><br>






<font  face="times new roman"><b><a href="http://www.nytimes.com/2001/11/22/opinion/22HERB.html?todaysheadlines">Hunger in the City</a></b>
<br>
By BOB HERBERT
<br>
There is something very wrong, in a society as affluent as ours, when families have to choose between food and rent.
<P>


<font  face="times new roman"><b><a href="http://www.nytimes.com/2001/11/22/opinion/22SAFI.html?todaysheadlines">Welcome Back, Politics!</a></b>
<br>
By WILLIAM SAFIRE
<br>
Here is the trick in political prognostication: Take what you know to be true and then play   fast and loose with the possible.
<P>
</font>


<font  face="times new roman"><b><a href="http://www.nytimes.com/2001/11/22/opinion/22SPER.html?todaysheadlines">Educating the World</a></b>
<br>
By GENE SPERLING
<br>
The United States should commit to getting all the world's children in school.
<P>
</font>









